  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Although lacking strong evidences, plasma transfusions are commonly used in critically ill
      neonates. To date, the relationships between plasma transfusions and nosocomial infection
      remain controversial and no study has reported the relationships between plasma transfusion
      and invasive fungal infection (IFI)
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Our aim is to explore the association between plasma transfusions and IFI in critically ill
      neonates
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
